Posts.Content: galwaygirl wrote: was at the doctors two weeks ago and she found a lump. referred me to get an ultrasound to be on the safe side.  getting a wee bit worried since then - i cant really feel the lump but have noticed that the veins in my breast are definately more prominent also slight change in my skin.  From looking up sites i have seen that a risk factor is having ur period early - i first started a month after my 10th birthday and i have been on the pill for 4 years now.  Any thoughts - is it a bad thing that i cant feel the lump?
